race.comment: TOPMOST (8) has had a few chances but looks well placed here third up from a good draw. The fresh run at Kyneton reads well when beaten half a length, solid again here last time when staying at 1200m. He gets to 1400m now and finds a winnable race. RICH KING (6) is one to watch on debut. He's a gelding by Rich Enuff for the Matt Laurie yard who has won a jumpout leading in. He draws well and should be ready to go. LISA LASS (9) resumes for her second campaign. She showed promise in four runs last time in and has claims. BOLSHIE (1) resumes for a new yard. He can mix his form but has put up a few runs that have him firmly in the mix so watch the market for a lead. KILFEARAGH (5) was okay on debut and can improve.
